### Is there an existing issue for this? - [X] I have searched the existing issues ### Bug description I keep getting an "ValueError: all input arrays must have the same shape" on the evaluation step during "Selecting best skeleton". I get the error when using the gui or running the evaluation with ipython. I'm able to see the evaluation results (MAEs and frames with labels plotted). I have gotten this error running two different maDLC projects on both Windows and Ubuntu. A few others have also reported getting this error. Also recently discussed on the forum: https://forum.image.sc/t/valueerror-all-input-arrays-must-have-the-same-shape/56420 ### Operating System Ubuntu 20.04 Windows 10 ### DeepLabCut version dlc version 2.2.0.1 ### DeepLabCut mode multi animal ### Device type gpu: GeForce GTX 1070 ### Steps To Reproduce 1. DEEPLABCUT environment (create according to installation instructions) 2. Create multianimal project, extract frames, label frames, check labels, train network 3. Run Evalution from gui or ipython 4.
